<h2 id="Share-a-persona-based-quiz-to-generate-leads-across-industries">8 lead generation ideas (with examples!) from marketing pros</h2>
<p>Our expert sources came through big time with an eclectic mix of lead gen examples. From quirky quizzes to creative comics, there&#8217;s an idea here for every type of business.</p>
<h3>1. Share a persona-based quiz to generate leads across industries</h3>
<p>The absolute best <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/15/lead-magnet-ideas">lead magnets</a> are hyper-relevant to the people you want to convert. But how do you make that happen when you sell a product that works for several industries?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/wren-noble/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wren Noble</a>, Content Marketing Lead at <a href="http://glideapps.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Glide</a>, says they focused on a personality trait their ideal customers share.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWhen we realized what set the Glide customer apart was their eagerness to innovate, we came up with a creative way to connect with them and learn more about what they value,‚Äù she says.</p>
<p>Glide‚Äôs no-code software helps businesses create apps. And what Glide‚Äôs customers value is innovation.</p>
<p>So Wren and the team built the <a href="https://url.us.m.mimecastprotect.com/s/1lUyCxkzRvCxGOM6JT8E5zz?domain=glideapps.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Innovator Quiz</a>.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-quiz-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Glide's Innovator Quiz" width="722" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81419 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-quiz-1.webp 722w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-quiz-1-480x399.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 722px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://innovators-quiz.glide.page/dl/d0a5f4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>After answering a few questions, the quiz assigns you one of four innovation styles: builder, strategist, optimizer, or scientist. It also points out some characteristics of each style.</p>
<p>The brilliance of this campaign is that it generates leads <em>and</em> drives new traffic through social networks. It really took off on LinkedIn, where people eagerly shared and commented on their results.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-linkedin.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - LinkedIn post about Glide's Innovator Quiz" width="525" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81418 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-linkedin.webp 525w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-glide-linkedin-480x549.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 525px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/reaserios_im-an-optimizer-my-innovation-is-efficient-activity-7161383616533450753-b9gK?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>That got more people curious to find their innovation style. ‚ÄúThe quiz started so many engaged conversations and helped us understand what our leads get truly excited about,‚Äù Wren says.</p>
<p>You can adapt this <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/lead-generation-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">lead generation idea</a> for any business and any audience. It doesn‚Äôt require a huge budget‚Äîjust a strong understanding of your target customers and a good <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/content-distribution">distribution strategy</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Lead generation pages need a compelling call to action. Download this free guide to see some of the <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download">best CTA examples ever written</a>.</p>
<div id="Exchange-a-custom-report-for-contact-details"></div>
<h3>2. Exchange a custom report for contact details</h3>
<p>According to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/varun-penamatsa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Varun Penamasta</a>, Digital Marketing Manager at <a href="http://freshpaint.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Freshpaint</a>, successful lead generation does not require complex calculus. You just need to solve a problem for your target customer.</p>
<p>&#8220;We&#8217;ve had a ton of lead gen success by centering on real value for our audience. In exchange for their info, we offer something our audience will use in their jobs,‚Äù he says.</p>
<p>Varun pointed to Freshpaint‚Äôs <a href="https://info.freshpaint.io/custom-web-tracker-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Tracker Report</a> as an <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/lead-generation-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">example of a winning lead generation strategy</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Freshpaint-report-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Freshpaint's report tracker." width="691" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81420 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Freshpaint-report-1.webp 691w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Freshpaint-report-1-480x417.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 691px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://info.freshpaint.io/custom-web-tracker-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Freshpaint‚Äôs customers are <a href="https://localiq.com/industries/healthcare/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">healthcare</a> organizations. They follow strict HIPAA rules about the data they collect and store from website visitors. The people who use the Web Tracker Report get a one-time audit of all the tracking snippets capturing data on each page of their website.</p>
<p>The genius here is that the Web Tracker is also a Freshpaint product. So, leads who get a report can also see the product in action.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWe use these site scans as a lead generation anchor because we know they provide a ton of value to healthcare teams. We also introduce Freshpaint as a value-add,‚Äù says Varun.</p>
<p>How can you adapt this <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/lead-generation-strategies">lead gen strategy</a> for your business? You could provide a sample or free trial in exchange for an email address. Or let leads use your product to solve one specific problem, with the promise that it can solve more once they sign up.</p>
<div id="Create-unexpected-and-on-brand-content-types-to-build-trust"></div>
<h3>3. Create unexpected and on-brand content to build trust</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/12/28/content-marketing-advice">Content marketing</a> is a proven lead-generation strategy. It builds trust so your new lead doesn‚Äôt hesitate to register or subscribe.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs easier said than done, especially if your audience distrusts overt marketing efforts. You need to get creative with content that stands out and resonates with your core audience.</p>
<p>We love this example from <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/elaine-atwell-a1b87710b/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elaine Atwell</a>, Content Manager at <a href="https://www.kolide.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kolide by 1Password</a>. Elaine produces a series of industry-related comics to connect with her skeptical audience of IT managers. She publishes them on LinkedIn, along with a link to the newsletter signup page.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-kolide-comic-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Kolide's comic" width="936" height="455" class="aligncenter wp-image-81421 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-kolide-comic-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-kolide-comic-1-480x233.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kolide-inc_attention-mac-and-windows-userswere-about-activity-7161385355529646080--INe?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>While the comics aren‚Äôt a lead magnet, Elaine says they‚Äôve helped increase newsletter subscriptions by 1000% over the last year.</p>
<p>‚ÄúPeople in our industry are very selective about which newsletters they subscribe to. But they really appreciate an opinionated, humorous tone. The comics set the stage for what subscribers will get in the newsletter.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Kolide-sub-page-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Kolides subscribe page." width="768" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81422 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Kolide-sub-page-1.webp 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Kolide-sub-page-1-480x375.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 768px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lp.kolide.co/kolidescope" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>By the time readers get to the signup page, they know they‚Äôll get interesting content that speaks their language, so subscribing is a no-brainer.</p>
<p>Elain‚Äôs content-first <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/01/content-marketing-funnel">marketing funnel</a> brings in leads because the team knows its audience well. They spend time roaming Reddit and talking to the sales team. This strategy can work for your business, too. Start by following your customers on <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/linkedin-banner/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media</a>, interacting with them in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/19/brand-community">online communities</a>, and listening to how they interact on sales calls.</p>
<div id="Build-a-free-tool-your-ideal-prospect-can‚Äôt-resist"></div>
<h3>4. Build a free tool your ideal prospect can&#8217;t resist</h3>
<p>A <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/wordstream-graders?camplink=mainnavbar&amp;campname=freetools">free tool</a> is a lead generation goldmine. Create it once, and it will sit on your site, passively attracting new customers for years. When you add <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/04/internal-linking">internal links</a> to your free tool in content and promote it on social media, the leads really get flowing.</p>
<p>What‚Äôs extra cool about a free tool is that it can also qualify <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/linkedin-ads-bidding">leads</a> for you. The people who use it are most likely your target customers.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.ajdinperco.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ajdin Perco</a>, Head of Content at <a href="https://www.animalz.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Animalz</a>, told us how they created <a href="https://revive.animalz.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Revive</a> to get leads from their audience of marketers. Revive uses Google Analytics data to find content that‚Äôs losing traffic on your blog. With that list in hand, you can refresh the posts so they rank higher on search engines and get more visits.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Animalz-revive-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - The Revive free tool." width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81423 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Animalz-revive-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Animalz-revive-1-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://revive.animalz.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></p>
<p>To start the process, people head to the Revive home page and enter their email address (new lead!). After giving access to their Google Analytics, they‚Äôll get a list of posts ripe for refreshing.</p>
<p>Ajdin says the tool‚Äôs so successful because it solves a core pain point‚Äîlost traffic‚Äîfor the people Animalz needs to convert. ‚ÄúI like it because it provides actionable output that users can act on. It lists articles worth refreshing, which is incredibly valuable and can lead to traffic growth.‚Äù</p>
<p>It‚Äôs no small lift to create a new tool, though. Go into it with a strong understanding of how it‚Äôll improve your ideal customer‚Äôs life. And have a solid plan to distribute it through social media, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">SEO</a>, and email.</p>
<div id="Use-direct-messages-to-get-new-leads-faster"></div>
<h3>5. Use direct messages to get new leads faster</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/01/09/social-media-marketing-strategies">Social media marketing</a> is a great way to connect with new prospects. However, most people have to click from the social media platform to your landing page to enter their contact details, which is not great since some of them won‚Äôt want to leave the social media site.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/larrykim/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Larry Kim</a>, CEO of <a href="http://customers.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Customers.ai</a> (formerly Mobile Monkey), told us how he used Instagram Messenger automation to collect leads right from Instagram.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how it worked. The Mobile Monkey team created a guide showing people<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/02/how-to-get-verified-on-instagram"> how to get verified on Instagram</a>‚Äîvaluable information for their target audience of brands and celebrities looking to grow their social media presence.</p>
<p>Then, they promoted the guide using <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/instagram-advertising">paid Instagram campaigns</a>. Anyone who replied with ‚ÄúVERIFIED‚Äù got the guide in their <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-dm-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">direct messages</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-mobile-monkey-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Instagram post from Mobile Monkey." width="897" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81424 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-mobile-monkey-1.webp 897w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-mobile-monkey-1-480x321.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 897px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CR87iQzFCpq/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Sliding into your customers&#8217; DMs can be creepy. But Larry and his team started the conversation by giving something useful people asked for. And since Instagram won‚Äôt let you place links on posts, they cut out a lot of lead-gen friction (no ‚Äúlink in bio‚Äù craziness).</p>
<p>‚ÄúIt just seemed like the offer of ‚Äòhow to get verified for free‚Äô resonated with people actively working on growing their IG presence,‚Äù Larry said. ‚ÄúPromoting it in an IG post with a call to action to comment on it and experience Instagram Direct Message automation was a great way to onboard prospective users.‚Äù</p>
<p>Larry used <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/08/05/b2b-marketing-automation-tactics">marketing automation</a> to reply to requests instantly. That‚Äôs a great way to scale this strategy. Follow up with everyone who replies so you don‚Äôt waste any leads. If time is tight, consider <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-in-marketing">using AI</a> to help answer everyone faster.</p>
<div id="Create-a-compelling-guide-from-original-data"></div>
<h3>6. Create a compelling guide from original data</h3>
<p>Yeah, we know using a guide to generate leads isn‚Äôt groundbreaking. But here‚Äôs the thing: they work! We recently ran a poll asking which <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/search-advertising-benchmarks/">type of lead generation</a> offer drove the most leads. <strong>Guides and ebooks won by a long shot</strong>!</p>
<p>But <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephanie-yoder/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephanie Yoder</a>, Director of Client Services at <a href="https://megawattcontent.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Megawatt</a>, says your guide better be good if you want someone to give up their email address. She suggests Arcadia as a business that‚Äôs writing exceptional <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/18/gated-content">gated content</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúSo many whitepapers out there are purely self-serving and, frankly, boring,‚Äù she says.‚ÄúBut I‚Äôm a big fan of Arcadia&#8217;s whitepapers because they connect to timely industry topics and provide actual value to potential readers.‚Äù</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an example Stephanie said she really likes. ‚ÄúThis paper on the solar buying experience uses original survey data to answer a real question for Arcadia‚Äôs customers. Namely, what do people want when they‚Äôre buying solar equipment?‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Arcadia-guide-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Arcadia's lead gen landing page" width="936" height="450" class="aligncenter wp-image-81425 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Arcadia-guide-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-Arcadia-guide-1-480x231.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.arcadia.com/resources/solar-buying-whitepaper" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The lead capture page asks for a little extra information, like job title and company name. These details can help when it‚Äôs time to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/05/13/targeted-email-marketing-strategies">segment your email audience</a>. And it‚Äôs not terribly personal information, so it shouldn‚Äôt be a big friction point.</p>
<p>As for gathering original data for a top-notch guide, you don‚Äôt have to commission a vast data study. You can interview a handful of industry leaders, run a half-dozen polls on LinkedIn, or mine your records for trends (just make sure what you show is anonymized). Then, couple that with existing stories and publicly accessible data to tell a complete and valuable story.</p>
<div id="Get-customers-to-qualify-themselves-with-a-product-quiz"></div>
<h3>7. Get customers to qualify themselves with a product quiz</h3>
<p>We‚Äôve seen how quizzes can break down the silos between your customers‚Äô industries. But <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lyndsay-cordell-2228077b/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lyndsay Cordell</a>, an SEO and Content Strategist working with <a href="http://faire.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Faire.com</a>, says they‚Äôre also great at educating new leads about your products.</p>
<p>By way of example, Lyndsay showed us this <a href="https://www.willowhillsoapcompany.com/pages/what-fragrance-is-best-for-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener">product quiz</a> from the <a href="https://www.willowhillsoapcompany.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Willow Hill Soap Company</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Willow Hill Soap Company quiz page." width="936" height="586" class="aligncenter wp-image-81426 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-1-480x301.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.willowhillsoapcompany.com/pages/what-fragrance-is-best-for-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The quiz is only a couple of questions long. People who complete it get a recommendation for a soap scent that‚Äôll suit them, plus a visceral description of the product.</p>
<p>Lyndsay says this tactic helps overcome the challenge of selling things people can‚Äôt fully experience from an online shop. ‚ÄúThe quiz uses descriptive language that helps customers pinpoint their fragrance preference. It‚Äôs a creative way to showcase fragrances, especially when smell-o-vision doesn‚Äôt exist.‚Äù</p>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/lead-capture/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lead capture</a> doesn‚Äôt actually take place on the quiz. Instead, quiz takers immediately see a discount popup on their results page.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-popup-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Willow Hill popup with discount." width="652" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-81428 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-popup-1.webp 652w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-willow-hill-popup-1-480x442.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 652px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.willowhillsoapcompany.com/pages/what-fragrance-is-best-for-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/08/04/interactive-content">Interactive content</a>, a valuable <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/22/popup-examples">popup</a> offer, and a personalized product recommendation are powerful lead-generation combos.</p>
<p>This is such a versatile and low-lift tactic. Consider what questions you‚Äôd ask a customer to help them pick a product. Post those in a quiz, add a popup offer, and boom! You‚Äôve got leads.</p>
<div id="Invite-experts-to-your-webinars-for-greater-reach"></div>
<h3>8. Invite experts to your webinars for greater reach</h3>
<p>Webinars are an easy way to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/02/03/repurposing-content">repurpose your best content</a>. Gather a few posts covering different aspects of the same theme and use them as webinar topics.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/susie-marino129/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Susie Marino</a>, our Senior Content Marketing Specialist, runs a monthly webinar that‚Äôs regularly one of our highest-performing lead generators. Some people learn better from video. As Susie presents the information in a fun and personal way, she‚Äôs engaging the portion of our audience that might not read a blog post.</p>
<p>Susie gets even more reach‚Äîand leads‚Äîby inviting an expert to sit in with her. For example, she recently had <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jenna-zeidan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jenna Zeidan</a>, Google‚Äôs Senior Strategic Manager, join to talk about upcoming search and social media trends.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-localiq-video-1.webp" alt="Lead generation examples - Screenshot of a webinar video." width="936" height="548" class="aligncenter wp-image-81429 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-localiq-video-1.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/lead-generation-examples-wordstream-localiq-video-1-480x281.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3M0BSHpWxSM" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Susie says having a guest with specific expertise gave the webinar a big boost. ‚ÄúJenna was great. She answered tough questions people had about SEO and search. Having someone from Google helped us promote the webinar and get more people to sign up.‚Äù</p>
<p>But there‚Äôs another reason to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/26/partner-marketing">partner up</a> on webinars. <em>You get access to your guest&#8217;s network</em>. ‚ÄúWhen you look for someone to invite, look for people with a following,‚Äù Susie says. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôll get exposure with their network, so it‚Äôs like an extra promotion channel.‚Äù</p>
<p>This idea doesn‚Äôt just work for webinars. Find a business that‚Äôs complementary to yours and co-create a guide or run a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/giveaway-ideas">giveaway</a> on social media. You‚Äôll double the exposure for the same effort.</p>
<h2>Find lead generation ideas for your business</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-lead-generation">Lead generation</a> is the top goal for most marketers, but getting people to give up their contact details is not always easy. No matter which ideas you try, remember that it&#8217;s a game of trading value. Give something your ideal customer can use, and they‚Äôll reward you with the ability to continue the conversion.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re having trouble generating leads, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo">contact us</a>, and we‚Äôll show you how we can help you get more leads fast.</p>
<p>In the meantime, here‚Äôs a recap of the eight creative lead generation ideas our expert marketers shared:</p>
<ol>
<li>Share a persona-based quiz to generate leads across industries</li>
<li>Exchange a custom report for contact details</li>
<li>Create unexpected and on-brand content types to build trust</li>
<li>Build a free tool your ideal prospect can&#8217;t resist</li>
<li>Use direct messages to get new leads faster</li>
<li>Create a compelling guide from original data</li>
<li>Get customers to qualify themselves with a product quiz</li>
<li>Invite experts to your webinars for greater reach</li>
</ol>
